title: For Sale:  JP Sauer 38H German Pistol
postcontent:
The Sauer 38H or often just H was a small semi-automatic pistol made in Nazi Germany from 1938 until just after the end of World War II by J. P. Sauer & Sohn, then based in Suhl, Germany. The "H" in the model number denotes "hammerless"—the pistol uses an internal hammer.  Its a beautiful collectors piece or an ideal concealed carry weapon.  The pistol also includes a leather after market holster designed to fit this model handgun.  Further pictures of this pistol are available upon demand. Purchasers must either be Nebraska residents with a valid purchase permit/concealed carry permit or transfer in/out of state via a licensed FFL. Shipping and handling for mail purchases is $40.

postcontent: Im offering my services to sharpen all knives, short or long. i will give your blade an edge so sharp you can shave with it! I will take a picture of the blade before sharpening it and after to give assurance that no damage/scratches occurred while it was in my possession. I go to school in Grand Junction, so i am there daily monday-thursday. I have 15+ years experience and am offering this service for extra funds while im going to school. If i receive a knife, please give me 48 hours to have it sharpened. It could be finished sooner, but i never know what my workload looks like at school through the week. I never use electronic sharpeners or V shaped fixed stones. I have 2 stones (medium/fine grit) i use frequently and a more coarse stone for really bad blades.  I normally charge $5 for a normal sized pocket knife in average condition. I may charge a few bucks more if the blade edge is below average or if the blade material is D2 machining steel. I do NOT sharpen serrated edges, so if you bring me a knife with one, i can sharpen the plain edge, but nothing else. postcontent:
Two years old, in great shape, no scratches or dings. Comes with the MOLLE pouch and manual. Genuine ACOG, not some eBay Chinese knock-off. This is the reticle that was designed for the 14.5" barrel 556 cartridge. If you have a SBR or pinned/welded 14.5", this is the right option. I had it on my lightweight PSA CHF upper, but my wife likes shooting without magnification. I'm getting a Microdot instead of this ACOG.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Beware of buyer JAY / JAMAL
postcontent:
Beware of a guy named Jay Millz or Jamal trying to buy or barter for a pistol.  His email is REDACTED and REDACTED.  He's either a felon, a fool, or possibly a flake, you decide.

We negotiated a reasonable deal on a handgun I have posted and he said he'd call me in the evening to set up a time and place to meet. Instead he started texting me endlessly at 2 AM from two different numbers asking for more pictures, trying to renegotiate the deal, and trying to meet in the morning instead. When he called me back in the morning to set up the meeting, he gave me a sob story about his car being broken down and tried to get me to meet him at his "nieces" house.  I refused and we set up a public place he could take the bus to. Then he complained he didn't have cash after all and offered to make up the balance in ammo. After waiting an hour at the spot with no word I tried calling, but both the cell phones he had texted/called me from weren't his and the people had no idea where Jamal was. He called me later that evening from a third number and said he had found a ride and offered to come to my house and throw in some extra ammo for the deal. I refused, once more set up a public place to meet and told him to call me once he was there and I'd drive over rather than waiting for him. Never heard from him again, thank God.

Seller beware! Whether he's trying to rob you (or worse), get a handgun because he can't legally buy one, or is just a total flake, it's probably best to stay away from this particular guy.

**Since originally posting this last week, I've had over 10 emails from people reporting similar experiences.  This guy's obviously active and desperate!**

title: For Sale/Trade:  Lee Precision Turret Press, dies, and brass
postcontent:
Excellent condition Lee precision 4-hole turret press kit with everything you need to start reloading 9mm and 45ACP rounds, minus the projectiles, primers, and powder. I recommend fin fur and feather for buying your consumables, they have great deals on all ball ammo bullets that they sell by weight. No instructions or reloading manuals come with the set. The instructions are online in pdf format and can be downloaded for free, or watch someone show you how to do it on YouTube. The 9mm and 45ACP carbide die sets come with load data for some of the most popular powders and bullet weights. I have hardly used the dies. 

I also have 600 to 700 brass, the majority of which have been tumbled. Mostly 45ACP and 40S&W,  around 250 each, around 100 9mm brass and some 380. Might be some odd rifle brass mixed in there. 

The kit is used. There is some surface rust on some of the metal pieces on the reloader but no damage. The dies are virtually brand new. The brass is almost all once fired with a few twice fired mixed in. 

I know how much the kit costs brand new, around $200 from amazon. The dies are also around $35 per set. Brass ranges in ammo but averages around $40 for 500 depending on caliber. I'm not looking to make money on selling the set, just recoup some of the cost of buying it myself. I'm looking into building an AR15,  so anyone looking to trade parts would be my first choice on a trade. 

My prices are always negotiable and I would except trades or a mix of trades and cash. I'm not going to be an a-hole about negotiating, if it's good its good and if it isn't that's fine - no harm done. If you have always wanted to get into reloading, this set is a great buy. I can't afford to reload because I tend to shoot a lot more when I do, in affect - causing me to spend more money. If you do shoot a lot or are just looking for a hobby,  it would be good for you. I live in Circleville,  South of Columbus,  but work in Columbus so I can bring it when I go to work if you live there. I'm willing to travel halfway in any direction within reason. I can provide my drivers license and ccw,  as well as current homeland security background check proof - but no materials able to be used for identity theft will be provided. Understand that I am a nice guy but will not be very nice at all if someone tries to rip me off. Email me to get a conversation going if you are interested,  then I can provide a mobile phone number. Anyone wanting pictures can look at them on amazon.

title: For Sale/Trade:  VZ2008 with extras
postcontent: I've got a VZ2008 that I have only fired about 60 rounds through. This is the civilian version of the Czechoslovakian VZ58 assault rifle that they used instead of the Kalashnikov. This is a very interesting rifle with some fascinating history, the Slovakian military still uses it and many were even shipped to the Cubans during the Cuban missile crisis. Comes with original box, bayonet and scabbard, Czechoslovakian sling, cleaning kit, surplus mag pouch with five 30 round mags. This fires the 7.62x39 round that most other AK style rifles use.  It's in very nice shape and is very accurate I just don't like the folding stock.
